    "body": "The design of smart contract is a Consensys Multisig. So, if I call executeTransaction it will fire Executed or ExecutionFailed. The case is that case where ExecutionFailed is a valid call with a internal tx failing, but outer works. This case is not what I want, and I dont want geth to give a estimstion for failing the internal transaction while with a slightly more gas it would not fail. You sugges changing the smart contract design so the outer tx fails aswell? ",
